OL,6,FHe continued: "We will learn the
OL,7,Flessons from this and we apologise to
OL,8,Fthe woman and the wider community who
OL,9,Fwere deeply affected.
OL,11,F"Anyone who has seen the footage of
OL,12,Fthis incident will be upset by how it
OL,13,Fescalated into a traumatic situation
OL,14,Ffor a mother and her child.
OL,16,F"Since this incident happened, we have
OL,17,Fstopped our involvement in supporting
OL,18,FTransport for London fare evasion
OL,19,Foperations, but we continue our
OL,20,Fpresence on the bus network tackling
OL,21,Fviolent crime."
